The unruly mob like wild men behave,
Applauding the slave,
His eyes running swiftly from seat to seat ;
But not a look of pity they meet,
From the vestals down to the scum of the Street
Every one his foe.
Then he sees in the foremost row
The Proconsul’s wife—
Revenge his maddened brain demands ;
And he arches his back and clenches his hånds;
