And forward they come with a granting howl,
With blood-shot eyes at the man they scowl.
Food for their starved-out bellies they crave!
Why not go ahead ! unarmed is the slave !
But lo ! they cower, draw back in fear—
The tigers appear !
With forepaws aloft they leap in,
One by one, displaying their velvety skin,
The huge cats snifiing the air,
Smelling with contempt, as it were,
